TITLE: Handling Navigation Control in Data Loaders with TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet illustrates how to control navigation within a data loader, including handling errors, redirections, and navigation cancellation using the NavigationResult class from vue-router.
SOURCE: https://github.com/posva/unplugin-vue-router/blob/main/docs/data-loaders/rfc.md#2025-04-21_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { NavigationResult } from 'vue-router'

export const useUserData = defineLoader(
  async (to) => {
    try {
      const user = await getUserById(to.params.id)

      return user
    } catch (error) {
      if (error.status === 404) {
        return new NavigationResult({ name: 'not-found', params: { pathMatch: '' } }
        )
      } else {
        throw error // aborts the vue router navigation
      }
    }
  }
)
```

