TITLE: VueFire Loader Usage Examples
DESCRIPTION: Shows different implementation patterns for VueFire data loader usage including collection paths, document references, and computed properties handling.
SOURCE: https://github.com/posva/unplugin-vue-router/blob/main/src/data-loaders/tests-defineLoader.md#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
defineVueFireLoader('/documents', () => useCollection(...))

defineVueFireLoader('/documents/[id]', (route) => {
  return useDocument(doc(collections('documents'), route.params.id))
})

defineVueFireLoader('/documents/[id]', (route) => {
  return useDocument(computed(() => doc(collections('documents'), route.params.id)))
})

defineVueFireLoader('/documents/[id]', ((route) => doc(collections('documents'), route.params.id)))
```

